HEADWORD: Pleadable
<hw>Plead"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of being
pleaded; capable of being alleged in proof, defense, or vindication;
<as>as, a right or privilege <ex>pleadable</ex> at law</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

